So the swishing sound of the strokes, and the desperate but unnatural screams, continued. 
"Go on, go on!" said the major. 
A young officer with a bewildered and pained expression on his face stepped away from the man and looked round inquiringly at the ad- jutant as he rode by. 
Prince Andrew, having reached the front line, rode along it. Our front line and that of the enemy were far apart on the right and left
